HEADWORD: Plumbagineous
<hw>Plum`ba*gin"e*ous</hw>
<pr>(pl⟦ucr⟧m`b⟦adot⟧*j⟦icr⟧n"⟦esl⟧*⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to natural order
(<ord>Plumbagine⟦ae⟧</ord>) of gamopetalous herbs, of which Plumbago is
the type. The order includes also the marsh rosemary, the thrift, and a
few other genera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plumbaginous</ent>⟦br⟧
